<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-25-0444 </DOCNO><TEXT>After briefly outlining the historical aspects of nuclear power from itsmilitary origins to reactors for power production, the current positionof nuclear power around the world is examined. Factors affecting nuclearpower programmes are discussed; these include economics, safety, healtheffects of radiation, the problems of decommissioning nuclear plants,the management of radioactive wastes and nuclear weapons proliferation.The future prospects for nuclear power are also discussed. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>